y":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T07:15:32.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>source: TheHackerNews<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://thehackernews.com/2017/05/wannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html?m=1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fthehackernews.com%2F2017%2F05%2Fwannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html%3Fm%3D1&d=9Q7dZ4qQrO6lHh1kJph63fiMucz1dB5Ms3PJ3VCnrF8%3D&h=d6863561\" target=\"_blank\">https://thehackernews.com/2017/05/wannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html?m=1</a></blockquote><br />\n要未boot過機先救到，好似係響memory裡面搵返條key出嚟。</blockquote><br />\n電腦專家教即刻熄機<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/10.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9e879ba494103ff672625d0841b169536cd35a18","tid":250212,"uid":105553,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T07:19:36.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>係咪代表全世界嘅加密都可以被解密？</blockquote><br />\n<br />\nNo.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Based on this finding, Guinet released a WannaCry ransomware decryption tool, named WannaKey, that basically tries to retrieve the two prime numbers, used in the formula to generate encryption keys from memory, and <span style=\"color: red;\">works on Windows XP only</span>.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n...<br />\n<br />\n&quot;So, that means, this method will work only if:<br />\nThe affected computer <span style=\"color: red;\">has not been rebooted after being infected</span>.<br />\nThe associated <span style=\"color: red;\">memory has not been allocated and erased by some other process.</span>&quot;<br />\n<br />\n就算部XP機唔boot，耐咗memory會reuse都係無咗條key。"},{"pid":"fad0309486ca142b7126938b1cfff385efe2e2ff","tid":250212,"uid":43308,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T07:22:11.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"af98e8a93c4a41e2ad2c7a827f12b3a124e12abe","tid":250212,"uid":105553,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T07:23:47.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>即係哂尻氣 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n凡事都有第一步，希望再有好D solution，不過過咗7日好多就救唔返。"},{"pid":"23412ac63011e2b481cb837d53824ee2cc09b413","tid":250212,"uid":23953,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T07:26:28.000Z","msg":"依個post咁都上到熱門<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/@.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"94ddee1b9e9a20d8a0bef735339e782f2b362c62","tid":250212,"uid":11001,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T07:26:28.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>係咪代表全世界嘅加密都可以被解密？</blockquote><br />\n<br />\nNo.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Based on this finding, Guinet released a WannaCry ransomware decryption tool, named WannaKey, that basically tries to retrieve the two prime numbers, used in the formula to generate encryption keys from memory, and <span style=\"color: red;\">works on Windows XP only</span>.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n...<br />\n<br />\n&quot;So, that means, this method will work only if:<br />\nThe affected computer <span style=\"color: red;\">has not been rebooted after being infected</span>.<br />\nThe associated <span style=\"color: red;\">memory has not been allocated and erased by some other process.</span>&quot;<br />\n<br />\n就算部XP機唔boot，耐咗memory會reuse都係無咗條key。</blockquote><br />\nGitHub個repo好似寫x86 Win XP/Server 2003/7都得 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e535bb56103bd973f2f58b556b6796f9cfaa3eb3","tid":250212,"uid":33874,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T07:40:18.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote><blockquote>source: TheHackerNews<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://thehackernews.com/2017/05/wannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html?m=1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fthehackernews.com%2F2017%2F05%2Fwannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html%3Fm%3D1&d=9Q7dZ4qQrO6lHh1kJph63fiMucz1dB5Ms3PJ3VCnrF8%3D&h=d6863561\" target=\"_blank\">https://thehackernews.com/2017/05/wannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html?m=1</a></blockquote><br />\n要未boot過機先救到，好似係響memory裡面搵返條key出嚟。</blockquote><br />\n電腦專家教即刻熄機<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/10.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n班友邊忽專家？死機就叫你reboot，壞機就叫你check電線有冇插好，再唔係就洗機買過部啦"},{"pid":"506d3dc09c342365a6c264630e9f68023c0a10e2","tid":250212,"uid":67527,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-20T11:00:03.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>係咪代表全世界嘅加密都可以被解密？</blockquote><br />\n<br />\nNo.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Based on this finding, Guinet released a WannaCry ransomware decryption tool, named WannaKey, that basically tries to retrieve the two prime numbers, used in the formula to generate encryption keys from memory, and <span style=\"color: red;\">works on Windows XP only</span>.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n...<br />\n<br />\n&quot;So, that means, this method will work only if:<br />\nThe affected computer <span style=\"color: red;\">has not been rebooted after being infected</span>.<br />\nThe associated <span style=\"color: red;\">memory has not been allocated and erased by some other process.</span>&quot;<br />\n<br />\n就算部XP機唔boot，耐咗memory會reuse都係無咗條key。</blockquote><br />\n其實無咩用，只要attacker做多一步，send完去server之後bzero，之後放新版本，基本上就會無咗依個漏洞"},{"pid":"6cc0a4704cf4c9ecb116bf26323cc6a4db65ba41","tid":250212,"uid":36478,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-05-23T10:39:01.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>source: TheHackerNews<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://thehackernews.com/2017/05/wannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html?m=1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fthehackernews.com%2F2017%2F05%2Fwannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html%3Fm%3D1&d=9Q7dZ4qQrO6lHh1kJph63fiMucz1dB5Ms3PJ3VCnrF8%3D&h=d6863561\" target=\"_blank\">https://thehackernews.com/2017/05/wannacry-ransomware-decryption-tool.html?m=1</a></blockquote><br />\n要未boot過機先救到，好似係響memory裡面搵返條key出嚟。</blockquote><br />\n仲有限好舊嘅XP版本"}]}